+Pre-exploration briefing request for Strategizer on mission `exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck`, strategy `strategy-001`, before exploration 001.
+
+Concrete question:
+This strategy starts with the Phase 0 canonical packet-object gate for the helical sign bottleneck mission. I need the most relevant local-library material for deciding whether one preferred exact-NS helical packet/sign object can actually be frozen canonically, rather than drifting among packet conventions.
+
+Please return only the material that directly helps answer:
+
+1. which local notes are most useful for fixing one preferred packet family for Tao-like roles, one support/refinement convention, one conjugate-pair representative quotient, and one desired-role graph without silently changing the object,
+2. which local notes most directly address the known packet canonization risks:
+   - packet support dependence,
+   - projection/coordinatization dependence,
+   - desired-vs-leakage bookkeeping drift,
+   - leakage scalarization drift,
+   - representative-choice dependence for global sign-coherence functionals,
+3. whether the library already contains anything that helps defend the two-function functional split suggested by the singleton sign prototype:
+   - global minority-helicity participation `SD_part`,
+   - desired-edge heterochirality defect `SD_target`,
+   and in particular whether any local note already says how these should behave under harmless packet refinements or representative relabelings,
+4. whether the best local evidence points toward a viable preferred packet object, a sharply defined backup only, or immediate canonicity failure,
+5. which meta guidance is most relevant for forcing exploration 001 to end with:
+   - one preferred packet/sign object and at most one backup,
+   - an explicit canonicity checklist,
+   - exact go/no-go criteria for the four mission outcomes,
+   - and an early stop if the object still moves under harmless refinements.
+
+Please be selective and concrete. If the local library still does not support a single theorem-facing packet/sign object for this mission, say that clearly so exploration 001 can treat canonicity failure as a live possible terminal result rather than pretending the object is already frozen.
+
