# Meta Note: Exploration 001

## What worked

- Treating Tao's delayed-transfer logic as a **localized interscale handoff** rather than as a five-role packet object immediately opened a faithful physical-space definition path. The exact NS filtered-energy budget gave the missing object.
- The right preferred event came from exact NS plus observability conventions, not from a reduced dynamical model. That sharply improved fidelity discipline at Phase 0.
- Keeping Duchon-Robert as backup but not preferred was the right level of ambition. It preserved a physical-space fallback without letting the mission drift into singularity-detection language too early.

## What to carry forward

- The next exploration should keep the exact same scale interface and witness channel and choose exactly one precursor observable tied to that interface.
- The main adversarial risk is not fidelity anymore; it is **Tao-specificity**. The next goal should force the explorer to explain why the chosen precursor is about delayed transfer rather than generic cascade activity.
- Filter choice, region geometry, and scale ratio are observability conventions. They need to be fixed early in Phase 1 so the precursor question stays one-object and theorem-facing.

## Execution note

- The launched explorer hit the common research-buffering stall: it created a skeleton report, searched the coarse-graining / Duchon-Robert literature, and did not write the synthesis. Manual recovery was straightforward because the source trail had already converged on the right object class.

